x^{\prime\prime} + x = ex^3
x(e, 0) = 1
x^{\prime}(e,0) = 0
O(e^3)
t \geq 0
x_0^{\prime\prime} + x_0 = 0
x_0 = A_0\cos t + B_0\sin t
x_0(0) = 1
x^{\prime}_0(0) = 0
x_0 = \cos t
x^{\prime\prime}_1 + x_1 = x_0^3
x_1 + x_1 = \cos^3 t
x^{\prime\prime}_1 + x_1 = \frac{3}{4}\cos t + \frac{1}{4}\cos 3t
x_1 = A\cos t + B\cos 3t
x^{\prime}_1 = -A\sin t - 3B\sin 3t
\ddot{x}_1 = -A\cos t - 9B\cos 3t
\ddot{x}_1 + x_1 = -8B\cos 3t = \frac{3}{4}\cos t + \frac{1}{4}\cos 3t
-8B = \frac{1}{4}
B = \frac{-1}{32}
x_1 = A\cos t - \frac{1}{32}\cos 3t
x_0(0) = 0
A = \frac{1}{32}
\frac{3}{8}t\sin t
 x(t) = x_0(t) + \varepsilon x_1(t) + \varepsilon^2 x_2(t) + ... 
 x_0'' + \varepsilon x_1 '' + \varepsilon^2 x_2 '' + ... + x_0 + \varepsilon x_1 + \varepsilon^2 x_2 + ... = \varepsilon (x_0 + \varepsilon x_1 + ... )^3 
 (x_0 + \varepsilon x_1 + ... )^3 = x_0^3 + 3 \varepsilon x_0^2 x_1 + \varepsilon^2 (3 x_0 x_1^2 + 3 x_0^2 x_2) + ... 
O(1)
x_0(0) = 1
x_0'(0) = 0
x_1(0) = x_1'(0) = x_2(0) = x_2'(0) = \ldots = 0.
x(t) = x_0(t) + \varepsilon x_1(t) + \varepsilon^2 x_2(t) + O(\varepsilon^3).
